    <item>
      <title>Free books for R beginners</title>
      <link>https://lbmii.github.io/resources/books/rbegin/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lbmii.github.io/resources/books/rbegin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Data science has taken the world by storm. Every field of study and area of business has been affected as people increasingly realize the value of the incredible quantities of data being generated. But to extract value from those data, one needs to be trained in the proper data science skills. The R programming language has become the de facto programming language for data science. Its flexibility, power, sophistication, and expressiveness have made it an invaluable tool for data scientists around the world. &lt;a href=&#34;https://bookdown.org/rdpeng/rprogdatascience/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;R Programming for Data Science&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is about the fundamentals of R programming. You will get started with the basics of the language, learn how to manipulate datasets, how to write functions, and how to debug and optimize code. With the fundamentals provided in this book, you will have a solid foundation on which to build your data science toolbox.&lt;/p&gt;
















&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-r-programming-for-data-science&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;R Programming for Data Science&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /media/rpdtsci_hu3b1d8d528246e07934ab64892479c2f4_129264_4f47215fce7a0f03fe47b4d6702b7657.webp 400w,
               /media/rpdtsci_hu3b1d8d528246e07934ab64892479c2f4_129264_87224f47f84f71a0737c9d44af656873.webp 760w,
               /media/rpdtsci_hu3b1d8d528246e07934ab64892479c2f4_129264_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://lbmii.github.io/media/rpdtsci_hu3b1d8d528246e07934ab64892479c2f4_129264_4f47215fce7a0f03fe47b4d6702b7657.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;281&#34;
               height=&#34;364&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption data-pre=&#34;Figure&amp;nbsp;&#34; data-post=&#34;:&amp;nbsp;&#34; class=&#34;numbered&#34;&gt;
      R Programming for Data Science
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://rstudio-education.github.io/hopr/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hands-On Programming with R&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will teach you how to program in R, with hands-on examples. The author wrote it for non-programmers to provide a friendly introduction to the R language. You’ll learn how to load data, assemble and disassemble data objects, navigate R environment system, write your own functions, and use all of R programming tools. Throughout the book, you’ll use your newfound skills to solve practical data science problems.&lt;/p&gt;
















&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-hands-on-programming-with-r&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Hands-On Programming with R&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /media/cohopr_hu6987db4b1b621fb3f9f1b8e2587c3ccd_28268_e063b9c14554a609184f66d9fa623ea5.webp 400w,
               /media/cohopr_hu6987db4b1b621fb3f9f1b8e2587c3ccd_28268_04e3deb7d6e7925e5161c7073dbc7cf5.webp 760w,
               /media/cohopr_hu6987db4b1b621fb3f9f1b8e2587c3ccd_28268_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://lbmii.github.io/media/cohopr_hu6987db4b1b621fb3f9f1b8e2587c3ccd_28268_e063b9c14554a609184f66d9fa623ea5.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;315&#34;
               height=&#34;413&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption data-pre=&#34;Figure&amp;nbsp;&#34; data-post=&#34;:&amp;nbsp;&#34; class=&#34;numbered&#34;&gt;
      Hands-On Programming with R
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Packages are the fundamental units of reproducible R code. They include reusable R functions, the documentation that describes how to use them, and sample data. In this book &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-pkgs.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;R Packages&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; you’ll learn how to turn your code into packages that others can easily download and use. Writing a package can seem overwhelming at first. So start with the basics and improve it over time. It doesn’t matter if your first version isn’t perfect as long as the next version is better.&lt;/p&gt;
















