    <item>
      <title>Gallery for R graphs and charts</title>
      <link>https://lbmii.github.io/resources/softwares/rgraphics/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 11 Aug 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lbmii.github.io/resources/softwares/rgraphics/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt; is a great tool for &lt;a href=&#34;%28https://www.data-to-viz.com/%29&#34;&gt;data visualization&lt;/a&gt;. The native tool becomes even better thanks to external packages such as &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/ggplot2/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;ggplot2&lt;/a&gt; that are widely used in the gallery. If you&amp;rsquo;re wondering what you can do with &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt; in terms of &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.data-to-viz.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;dataviz&lt;/a&gt;, the following online resources may help you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.data-to-viz.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;From Data to Viz&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a classification of chart types based on input data format. It comes in the form of a decision tree leading to a set of potentially appropriate visualizations to represent the dataset. The project is built on two underlying philosophies. &lt;em&gt;First&lt;/em&gt;, that most data analysis can be summarized in about twenty different dataset formats. &lt;em&gt;Second&lt;/em&gt;, that both data and context determine the appropriate chart. Thus, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.data-to-viz.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;From Data to Viz&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; suggested method consists in identifying and trying all feasible chart types to find out which suits your data and idea best. Once this set of graphics is identified, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.data-to-viz.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;From Data to Viz&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; aims to guide you toward the best decision. It also provides a list of common caveats to avoid and always provides a reproducible code snippet in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R programming language&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.data-to-viz.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dataviz&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a world with endless possibilities and this project does not claim to be exhaustive. However, it should provide you with a good starting point.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-charts.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;R CHARTS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; web site has been created without any financial support by José Carlos Soage. It was generated with &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/blogdown/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;blogdown&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/available_packages_by_name.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R package&lt;/a&gt; which allows creating static web sites using the HUGO generator. The theme of this site is a custom theme inspired by Kross and Academic themes. The classification of the charts is based on the Financial Times visual vocabulary. On the site of &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-charts.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;R CHARTS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; you will find code examples of &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt; graphs made with base &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt; graphics, &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/ggplot2/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;ggplot2&lt;/a&gt; and other &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/available_packages_by_name.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R package&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://r-graph-gallery.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;R graph gallery&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a collection of charts made with the &lt;a href=&#34;https://r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R programming language&lt;/a&gt;. Charts are organized by family and types. Hundreds (~ 400 charts) of charts are displayed in several sections, always with their reproducible code and explanations available. The gallery makes a focus on the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.tidyverse.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;tidyverse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/ggplot2/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;ggplot2&lt;/a&gt;. For each chart, a focus is made on code, but a link toward &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.data-to-viz.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;data-to-viz&lt;/a&gt; is provided to give more information concerning the theory.&lt;/p&gt;
